	   <tr><td colspan=2>Kill things before they kill you.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Seriously, go to Qeynos, level as far as you can get there.  Then you can move out to the Hills if you like.  When that gets dull, and it does not take long, I assure you, go to Field of Bone.  YOu can solo there to 17 or so if you are patient, but I imagine that you would have by this tme moved to a better zone, maybe Kurn's Tower if you don't have FDing monks training you right and left.  <br><br>At this point, you simply must make a friend or several, cause that crummy root will stick only as long as you don't blast it (isn't THAT a nice bit of irony).  My partner is a mage, and the pet is rather a handy fellow to have about when root breaks (means I can run like a fool while the pet finished it off, in my own brand of fear-kiting, the fear being my own terror that the target will actually get a slap in on me.  Somewhere in your 20s you will get a snare, and that makes soloing a realistic possibility once again.  My wizard is only in her 30s, so I can't help you beyond that.<br><br>At this level, I like the north end of the Overthere, and I stay there until I am ready to venture into Warsliks Woods.  This is a nice quiet zone with no sand giants.  I just stopped using that zone,and I haven't decided where to go from there.  <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
