	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104731660038381><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104731660038381>RE: Quadding</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104731660038381#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=206683><span id= >Rarespawn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 10th 12:50 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>While not necessarily a good response to your quadding question, partly because I suggest you wait until you get Circle of Force at 34, I suggest you get KEI and hunt in the Overthere.&nbsp;&nbsp;It might be a little tough at 29, but you can solo evens and yellows with BoF, a little root and nuke, and have Tishan's Clash handy as well.  I got through 32 and 33 there very quickly taking on sarnaks, cacti, cockatrices, etc.  It doesn't hurt to have jboots or some SoW potions, and for as fast as the experience was coming, was definitely worth the money for the potions at the time.  <br>If you're really intent on quading pre-Circle of Force, I would also try LOIO, or Marus Seru.  I can tell you that quadding with some, or even all, light-blues in groups is not necessarily a bad thing.  You're still getting multiple kills in a pretty quick time, and the experience isn't bad.  I have been quadding Ulthork hunters in EW (for the tusks), many of which were light blue at 41 and 42, but the experience has still come in pretty quickly.  Hope this helps.  Good luck in your hunting.<br><br>Hycliff, 42 wiz<br>Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
